cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is about unsupervised deep representation learning and clustering of deep features, which are common topics in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of deep self-expressive representation and adaptive locality preserving feature learning, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper presents comparison results on public databases, which suggests that it may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
